e class you interate with to draw scrolling text to the screen.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Once the layout is .scrolled you must send one configure message to tell the layout how to setup.  It will setup the slice height and how many slices are visible."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"There are two supported modes: autoScroll on\/off","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"When autoScroll is true, the slices are automatically scrolled.  Subscribe to the delgate and listen for the scrolled callback, when you get it send another slice of text","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"When autoScroll is false, you can drive the slices and how they look on the screen.  You can send all the slices at once or send one at a time and animate it onto the screen at the current time."}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://ultralitesdk.UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout/sendImage(image:slicePosition:scrollFirst:)":{"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/sendimage(image:sliceposition:scrollfirst:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/ultralitesdk.UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/sendImage(image:slicePosition:scrollFirst:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"sendImage"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"image","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"CGImage","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@CGImageRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"slicePosition","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"scrollFirst","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"title":"sendImage(image:slicePosition:scrollFirst:)","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abs